The quantitative relationship between the increased fluorescence intensity and the l-Cys concentration also could be used to realize the detection of l-Cys. As shown in Fig. S4a, a gradual increase in fluorescence intensity at 440 nm was observed with the increase of l-Cys concentration in the range of 0 to 0.24 mM. Fig. S4b presents the relationship between the concentration of l-Cys and the change of fluorescent intensity ((I-I0)/I0
                        ) of SiQDs/Cu2-β-CD nanoclusters solution. A satisfactory linearity relationship was observed in the range of 0.013–0.240 mM with a correlation coefficient of 0.9997. The linear regression equation can be represented as (I-I0)/I0
                         = 1.4382CL-Cys-4.956*10-4. The limit of detection (LOD) was estimated to be 0.48*10-3 mM based on three times the standard deviation rule. Table S1 shows the linear ranges and LOD of this method for l-Cys determination, which are comparable to or better than those of some other fluorescent probes.
